Key Match Events: Mohamed Abou Gabal missed his penalty in the shootout
Lionel Mpasi scored against Mohamed Abou Gabal in the shootout
Egypt bowed out at the Laurent Pokou Stadium
Meschack Elia gave DRC the lead when he headed in virtually on the goalline
Mostafa Mohamed scored his fourth goal of the tournament from the penalty spot on the stroke of half-time
Mohamed Hamdy received a red card in extra time
The game went to a shootout with DRC winning 8-7
Post-Match Reflections: Jonathan Wilson noted that the journeyman French coach is fast becoming an endangered species in Africa
Guinea coach Kaba Diawara said it was a very satisfying victory for his players
Guinea’s coach expressed satisfaction with his team’s performance despite previous criticism
Miscellaneous Highlights: Mohamed Salah will remain with Liverpool and not have to return to Ivory Coast as he continues to recover from a hamstring injury
A poor-quality game looked destined for extra time in Abidjan
Equatorial Guinea should have taken the lead from the penalty spot but Nsue’s shot hit a post
